  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "A 67-year-old man with a 20-year history of type 2 diabetes and hypertension is hospitalized with a 3-day history of fever, left-flank pain, urinary frequency, and malaise. He is treated for presumed pyelonephritis with ciprofloxacin 400 mg intravenously every 12 hours. Subsequent Gram stain of the urine reveals many gram-negative bacilli. On hospital day 3, the patient remains febrile; blood and urine cultures are positive for Escherichia coli.\nA CT scan of the abdomen is obtained and shows a large mixed-attenuation mass arising from the upper pole of the left kidney (figure).\nWhich one of the following management steps is most appropriate for this patient?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Perform nephrectomy"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Add intravenous cefepime"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Add intravenous vancomycin"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Perform percutaneous catheter drainage"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Add intravenous gentamicin"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 4,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>For <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">abscesses</a> ≥3 cm in size or those accompanied by <span data-sememe-id=\"3LdSxq0\">hemodynamic instability</span> due to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xm0E3g&anker=Zb3de189fac0d57eac5b7798e127a5e19\" data-learningcard-id=\"xm0E3g\" data-anker=\"Zb3de189fac0d57eac5b7798e127a5e19\" data-sememe-id=\"YNan-k\">sepsis</a>, percutaneous catheter drainage or surgical <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ki0Usf&anker=Za80c38a569c922fe143fe41bce9650b7\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ki0Usf\" data-anker=\"Za80c38a569c922fe143fe41bce9650b7\" data-section-id=\"RBal0M\" data-sememe-id=\"3ibSrt\">nephrectomy</a> are indicated. Percutaneous drainage is preferred, as it has a lower <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Js0sDh&anker=Z2b1819a683edfddebfad28cb21d64b9f\" data-learningcard-id=\"Js0sDh\" data-anker=\"Z2b1819a683edfddebfad28cb21d64b9f\" data-section-id=\"9fWNok0\" data-sememe-id=\"Esa89N\">morbidity</a> than <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ki0Usf&anker=Za80c38a569c922fe143fe41bce9650b7\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ki0Usf\" data-anker=\"Za80c38a569c922fe143fe41bce9650b7\" data-section-id=\"RBal0M\" data-sememe-id=\"3ibSrt\">nephrectomy</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>The addition of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z7dbf771bb5cba0042a1dc93dad471b17\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z7dbf771bb5cba0042a1dc93dad471b17\" data-section-id=\"WjcPzX0\" data-sememe-id=\"OJYI8J\">cefepime</a> to the patient's regimen would not change the response rate in this scenario because the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">abscess</a> is too large.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>The addition of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z6a6dc6e53c8a4895f4c3b5b2ff2a20b2\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z6a6dc6e53c8a4895f4c3b5b2ff2a20b2\" data-section-id=\"djcozX0\" data-sememe-id=\"GOaBFk\">vancomycin</a> to the patient's regimen would not change the response rate in this scenario because the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">abscess</a> is too large.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) CORRECT:</h4>Medical management with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\">antibiotics</a> alone is generally sufficient for treating renal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">abscesses</a> smaller than 3 cm. For <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">abscesses</a> ≥3 cm in size or those accompanied by <span data-sememe-id=\"3LdSxq0\">hemodynamic instability</span> due to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xm0E3g&anker=Zb3de189fac0d57eac5b7798e127a5e19\" data-learningcard-id=\"xm0E3g\" data-anker=\"Zb3de189fac0d57eac5b7798e127a5e19\" data-sememe-id=\"YNan-k\">sepsis</a>, percutaneous catheter drainage or surgical <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ki0Usf&anker=Za80c38a569c922fe143fe41bce9650b7\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ki0Usf\" data-anker=\"Za80c38a569c922fe143fe41bce9650b7\" data-section-id=\"RBal0M\" data-sememe-id=\"3ibSrt\">nephrectomy</a> are indicated. Percutaneous drainage is preferred, as it has a lower <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Js0sDh&anker=Z2b1819a683edfddebfad28cb21d64b9f\" data-learningcard-id=\"Js0sDh\" data-anker=\"Z2b1819a683edfddebfad28cb21d64b9f\" data-section-id=\"9fWNok0\" data-sememe-id=\"Esa89N\">morbidity</a> than <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ki0Usf&anker=Za80c38a569c922fe143fe41bce9650b7\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ki0Usf\" data-anker=\"Za80c38a569c922fe143fe41bce9650b7\" data-section-id=\"RBal0M\" data-sememe-id=\"3ibSrt\">nephrectomy</a>.<br><br>Renal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">abscesses</a> manifest in a similar fashion to acute, severe <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Hi0KGf&anker=Z9b1fc059a71fe47b61063c80c81af8c3\" data-learningcard-id=\"Hi0KGf\" data-anker=\"Z9b1fc059a71fe47b61063c80c81af8c3\" data-sememe-id=\"ZN0Z-T\">pyelonephritis</a> and should be considered if a patient with presumed <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Hi0KGf&anker=Z9b1fc059a71fe47b61063c80c81af8c3\" data-learningcard-id=\"Hi0KGf\" data-anker=\"Z9b1fc059a71fe47b61063c80c81af8c3\" data-sememe-id=\"ZN0Z-T\">pyelonephritis</a> does not improve after 3 days of appropriate <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\">antibiotic therapy</a>. There is a high <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Js0sDh&anker=Zbec41b67d43f63664a35843488324e30\" data-learningcard-id=\"Js0sDh\" data-anker=\"Zbec41b67d43f63664a35843488324e30\" data-section-id=\"9fWNok0\" data-sememe-id=\"JvbsaD\">mortality rate</a> among patients with large renal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">abscesses</a> in whom drainage is delayed. After percutaneous drainage, the total duration of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\">antimicrobial therapy</a> is determined by the patient's response, as assessed by clinical, laboratory, and radiological findings.<br><br><span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Key learning point:</b></span> The optimal treatment for large renal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">abscesses</a> is percutaneous catheter drainage.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>The addition of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Zc99c821ceb30bd08424f2808f57fe8b9\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Zc99c821ceb30bd08424f2808f57fe8b9\" data-section-id=\"hjccZc0\" data-sememe-id=\"qOaCtk\">gentamicin</a> to the patient's regimen would not change the response rate in this scenario because the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">abscess</a> is too large.</div>",
